### 1. Register a user (to generate credentials)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "courier@localkart.com",
  "password": "courierpassword",
  "name": "Delivery Agent"
}

###

### 2. Log in to get the JWT Token
# @name login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "courier@localkart.com",
  "password": "courierpassword"
}

###

@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 3. Get all delivery logs (Authenticated)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/deliveries
X-Auth-User: courier@localkart.com
X-Auth-Roles: ROLE_ADMIN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 4. Create a delivery manually (Admin/System only)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/deliveries
Content-Type: application/json
X-Auth-User: courier@localkart.com
X-Auth-Roles: ROLE_ADMIN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "orderNumber": "ORD-DELIV-999",
  "username": "customer@localkart.com",
  "courier": "LocalKart Express",
  "deliveryAddress": "123 Main St, Metro City, Country"
}

###

### 5. Fetch a specific delivery (Authenticated)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/deliveries/1
X-Auth-User: courier@localkart.com
X-Auth-Roles: ROLE_ADMIN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 6. Fetch a delivery by order number
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/deliveries/order/ORD-DELIV-999
X-Auth-User: courier@localkart.com
X-Auth-Roles: ROLE_ADMIN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7. Update delivery tracking status (e.g. SHIPPED)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/deliveries/1/status
Content-Type: application/json
X-Auth-User: courier@localkart.com
X-Auth-Roles: ROLE_ADMIN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "SHIPPED"
}
